nient to the central train station and a few good restaurants. The rooms are not clean and actually have mold there.  We had to move rooms twice and even in their nicest room, we had issues. The gentleman behind the desk in the evenings is very unpleasant. I fell and hurt myself because the air conditioner in our room dripped a big puddle of water and he didn\u2019t even care. Tried to report issues and no response. There are many others hotels nearby that I would try out next time.", "time": 1755952002, "translated": false}, {"author_name": "S P", "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100368813460608232221/reviews", "language": "en", "original_language": "en", "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJIxmQDR7YSf9YiqjF84xOBa7NyOYqcr_p4DJw4AFtziT2m7Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", "rating": 5, "relative_time_description": "a month ago", "text": "Thank you. They are the best. Super cosy hotel in a convenient location. The Mister in the entrance is very helpful and nice. I had lost an item in the train station and he was readily available to support.\nI recommend this hotel.", "time": 1755029564, "translated": false}, {"author_name": "Leanne Cryer", "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117991354699695165646/reviews", "language": "en", "original_language": "en", "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK_YTcffeRwHenRoQ1gDLZzBD_rTrK-kSC_NOxYTBY542Q9Ww=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2", "rating": 5, "relative_time_description": "a month ago", "text": "We were well looked after by Igor and the team at Hotel Bernina.  The room was spotless and just what we needed.   Igor the manager was very warm and helped us navigate around Milan.   We had a lovely breakfast and most importantly it was super close to Milan centrally which made for an easy commute with suitcases.   30mins walk to Duomo or the metro is 1 min away and an easy trip.  Highly recommend.  Thank you", "time": 1756215543, "translated": false}, {"author_name": "Kunaal Tailor", "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115646771014421687324/reviews", "language": "en", "original_language": "en", "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbrCpjjNFsL1rVssLkULesWfRHrwuHoNDsWeoaBi8G_9mquw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4", "rating": 3, "relative_time_description": "2 months ago", "text": "Location is excellent because you can even walk to the centre if you want. I did it, and it's really not far. Reception staff 5* but the room given was right by elevator noisy and thin walls. Hearing everyone come up and down. The condition of the bathroom was nothing like the pictures. But I still liked the room it was big enough. Noise and the elevator didn't bother me so much. However, what left a really sour taste is the horrendously rude lady at breakfast. Who gave me a dirty look when I asked her for another espresso, literally ignoring me and chatting in her mother tongue like she's not there working. Her behaviour is absolutely appalling. I've never had such poor treatment in a hotel. Paying over \u00a3100 per night it's unacceptable. Especially after paying a lot. Price not worth it cos of her. Otherwise, I was happy. Lots of nice shops and restaurants. Easy to reach the airport too. Everyone in Milan was so nice except for the horrible lady at breakfast.", "time": 1753818699, "translated": false}, {"author_name": "Jo\u00e3o N\u00f3brega", "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105017570558617050644/reviews", "language": "en", "original_language": "en", "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI8FVsLJMdhGY1Ikdvu9VppwFZmr5OX-cNGfxJ6kcNT2ykkFcY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo", "rating": 5, "relative_time_description": "4 months ago", "text": "Stayed here 5 days. 2 days in Milan and 3 days for day trips, location is a big plus since is near the train station.\n\nStaff are very friendly and competent. They all speak english very well.\n\nRoom was very clean. A bit small and it was quite hot ( glad it had air conditioning ). Bathroom was also immaculate.\n\nBreakfast is also top notch, big variety of pastries and breads.\n\nOverall very satisfying experience!!", "time": 1749049518, "translated": false}], "secondary_opening_hours": [{"open_now": false, "periods": [{"close": {"date": "2025-10-12", "day": 0, "time": "1000"}, "open": {"date": "2025-10-12", "day": 0, "time": "0700"}}, {"close": {"date": "2025-10-06", "day": 1, "time": "1000"}, "open": {"date": "2025-10-06", "day": 1, "time": "0700"}}, {"close": {"date": "2025-10-07", "day": 2, "time": "1000"}, "open": {"date": "2025-10-07", "day": 2, "time": "0700"}}, {"close": {"date": "2025-10-08", "day": 3, "time": "1000"}, "open": {"date": "2025-10-08", "day": 3, "time": "0700"}}, {"close": {"date": "2025-10-09", "day": 4, "time": "1000"}, "open": {"date": "2025-10-09", "day": 4, "time": "0700"}}, {"close": {"date": "2025-10-10", "day": 5, "time": "1000"}, "open": {"date": "2025-10-10", "day": 5, "time": "0700"}}, {"close": {"date": "2025-10-11", "day": 6, "time": "1000"}, "open": {"date": "2025-10-11", "day": 6, "time": "0700"}}], "type": "BREAKFAST", "weekday_text": ["Monday: 7:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fAM", "Tuesday: 7:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fAM", "Wednesday: 7:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fAM", "Thursday: 7:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fAM", "Friday: 7:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fAM", "Saturday: 7:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fAM", "Sunday: 7:00\u2009\u2013\u200910:00\u202fAM"]}], "types": ["establishment", "lodging", "point_of_interest"], "url": "https://maps.google.com/?cid=6984463899135129123", "user_ratings_total": 1056, "utc_offset": 120, "vicinity": "Via Napo Torriani, 27, Milano", "website": "https://www.hotelbernina.com/"}